HEADWORD: Hypospadias
<hw>Hy`po*spa"di*as</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>"ypo`</grk> beneath + <grk>spa`n</grk> to draw, tear.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A deformity of the penis, in which the urethra
opens upon its under surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

